description:
My place is good for couples, solo adventurers, business travelers, families (with kids), and furry friends (pets).

Beautiful cozy brownstone apartment situated in Park slope. Walk out of your apartment to restaurants, and bars minutes away. One bedroom, with closet space, television, full kitchen, and washer/dryer. 3 blocks from train to Manhattan or queens, citi-bikes to explore neighborhood are around the corner from apartment. Sofa bed is not a pull out couch just in case you plan on bringing a friend. We are pet friendly but PLEASE let us know prior that you plan on bringing a pet. We are very kind people and if our price is over you're budget we can work with you. We hope we are able to accommodate you on your vacation.

A few things you need to know;

To enter the apt. it is completely secure with a code that will be given once reservation is completed along with a key to the home. 

There is no elevator and you will need to walk up the stairs, which is something to take into account if you plan on traveling with heavy luggage.

We are both here to help plan you're stay every step of the way. If there is anything we can do to accommodate you or make you're stay more amazing than it will be we will do our best!


Please be respectful to our home and neighbors.

Quiet block in park slope close to bars and restaurants.

Train to Manhattan/Queens a few blocks away. Citi-bikes are around the corner.

Our apartments is very laid back but we have a strict policy of no smoking inside. I suffer from asthma and it is very important this rule is followed. 

Pet policy is lenient and for cleanliness purposes we prefer no pets but if you plan on traveling with a furry friend or cat let us know and we will try to work something out.


Please respect our home as if you would you're own.
You will have to walk up stairs to get to our apartment.

hosts.about:
My husband and I live in park slope and joined the airbnb host community. We both are very caring people and hope to make you're stay as enjoyable and memorable as possible. We hold our clients happiness as our top priority and if things aren't perfect we will try out best to correct it to make it as close as we can to you're standards. I've worked as a nurse for five years in the emergency room and operating room. I'm a certified scuba diver, sky diving enthusiast and a complete nerd who secretly enjoys calculus, organic chemistry, and extra cheese pizza.
Life is short and must be lived to full capacity which is why we travel the world together. From Europe to Thailand we love exploring cultures and getting to taste all the food that different countries offer. I hope my husband and I can accommodate you during you're travels to New York and make you're trip a memorable experience.

My wife and I are both Brooklynites having lived in Brooklyn for many years. We both are seekers of adventrue and spend a lot of time traveling the world. When I'm not in the office and she's not working as a nurse in the emergency room we love to go diving together. We both are certified scuba divers and have spent a lot of time under the sea and inside caverns! When we're not diving or traveling we're eating! Who doesn't love good food?! We love to splurge on the greater things in life and treat ourselves every so often to that amazing spa day that every couples needs every now and then. While my wife is a huge bookworm I deviate to watching friends and two and a half men! I think we're a pretty awesome team that are here to make sure you're stay is as close to perfect as possible! We hope we can accommodate you on you're travels to New York and will try our best to make you have the most amazing experience one could ask for!
